            . I am the wife of John Weston. These articles are mine; I had left them in a clothesbasket, in the back kitchen - they were all wet.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going by - the door was open; I went to go into the yard - I saw a man, and turned back; I met this young woman - she got the officer, and gave charged of me.</p>
               <p>GEORGE WYATT. I am the officer. I took the prisoner, and found some other property on her.</p>
